-Assigment operators: =+
-Escape chars: *n
-Single statement allowed as function definition
-No types
-No XOR in PDP-11 implementation?
-No for? no do-while? no break/continue?
-Required parens around return
-Architecture-dependent multi-chars (this is in C too!! C char literals are actually INTS, not chars--but they _are_ chars in C++)
-Triple === : equality assignment
-All functions are global?
-Auto required
